 unity and success. Teachers United also shows how NYSUT has been a leader of educational reform, winning more money for education, creating smaller classes, raising academic standards, and training better teachers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aTeacherszNew York (State)zNew York. 0aTeachers' unionszNew York (State)zNew York. 4aEducation : Education Policy and Leadership. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : History of Education. 4aHistory : History. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791479599423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791479599/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles